Frequently asked questions
--------------------------

What is a team member?

![Image 32](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

A team member is a paid user of Process Street that can create, edit and run workflows and author and share pages.

Who can use the Startup plan?

![Image 33](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

We support the startup community by providing a significantly reduced price on the Pro Plan for businesses that have less than 15 employees and under $2 million in revenue.

Do you have any discounts?

![Image 34](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

We offer discounts for registered non-profits. [Contact us](https://www.process.st/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#99eaece9e9f6ebedd9e9ebf6fafceaeab7eaed "Process Street support") to find out more.

Is my data secure?

![Image 35](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

Yes, we take security very seriously. See our [security page](https://www.process.st/security/ "Process Street security page").

Can I try out Pro features?

![Image 36](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

All new accounts start with a complimentary 14-day trial of our Pro plan, so that you can create as many workflow and workflow runs as you need to. Once the trial ends, you can buy Process Street to continue using it.

Can I get a demo of Process Street?

![Image 37](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

Yes, [book a demo](https://www.process.st/pricing/# "Request a Process Street demo").

How can I pay?

![Image 38](https://www.process.st/wp-content/themes/koombea/images/fa-chevron.svg)

We accept all major credit cards, charged in USD. Additionally, invoicing is available on the Pro and Enterprise plans.

Take control of your workflows today
